# IMPORT ORDER

## STANDARD ORDER (Spotless/Palantir Java Format)
Order enforced by Spotless in `build.gradle`:
1. `java.*` - Java standard library
2. `javax.*` - Legacy Java extensions
3. `jakarta.*` - Jakarta EE (replaces javax)
4. `org.*` - Third-party libraries (Spring, Jmix, etc.)
5. `com.*` - Third-party libraries
6. `com.digtp.*` - Project packages
7. Static imports last

## DETAILED ORDERING WITHIN GROUPS

### Java Standard Library
- `java.util.*` (Collections, Lists, Maps, etc.)
- `java.io.*` (I/O operations)
- `java.time.*` (Date/time API)
- Other `java.*` packages

### Framework Imports
- `org.springframework.*` - Spring Framework (Boot, Security, Test, etc.)
- `io.jmix.*` - Jmix Framework (Core, FlowUI, Security, etc.)
- `com.vaadin.*` - Vaadin Framework
- Other `org.*` and `com.*` third-party libraries

### Project Imports
- `com.digtp.start.*` - Project-specific packages

## EXAMPLES

### ✅ CORRECT ORDER
```java
